ATT_REQUESTOR

public static final java.lang.String ATT_REQUESTOR
A standard attribute name used to represent the person that initiated the request. This can be an Identity name or something abstract like "system".

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ATT_EVENT_TYPE

public static final java.lang.String ATT_EVENT_TYPE
A standard attribute used to represent a subtype of "event" requests. An "event" is just a Request that uses the WorkflowRequestExecutor to do something and is owned by an Identity. There can be several types of identity events, one is for role assignment sunrise/sunset.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ATT_RESTARTS

public static final java.lang.String ATT_RESTARTS
An attribute set by RequestProcessor to the number of times this request has been restarted.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

ATT_PARTITION_RESULT

public static final java.lang.String ATT_PARTITION_RESULT
Attribute that can contain a private TaskResult for partitioned tasks. This is an alternative to the single shared TaskResult that contains a list of partition results. This is an test to see why large numbers of partitions behave badly, possibly due to contention on the shared result.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

PHASE_NONE

public static final int PHASE_NONE
Special value for the dependentPhase property that means this request can run immediately even if there are requests with a lower phase.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

PHASE_PENDING

public static final int PHASE_PENDING
Special value for the dependentPhase property that means this request will never run until the dependentPhase is changed manually.

getNextLaunch

public java.util.Date getNextLaunch()
The desired date of execution for this request.

For normal requests this starts out null which causes it to execute immediately. Then it will be set only if a retry is needed.

For event requests this is set initially to a date in the future.
